@isbool(x)
	Returns "true" if 'x' is truthy or falsey, or "false" otherwise.\n\nTruthy values are "true", "t", "yes", "y", "1", "-1", ignoring case.\nFalsey values are "false", "f", "no", "n", "0", and "", ignoring case.\n\n"null" is neither truthy or falsey and will return "false".
@isfalse(x)
	Returns "true" if 'x' is falsey or "false" otherwise.\n\nFalsey values are "false", "f", "no", "n", "0", and "", ignoring case.\n\n"null" is neither truthy or falsey and will return "false". Any invalid value will return "false".\n\nThis is exactly the same as "@false(x)".
