@swap(key1,key2)
	Swaps the values between key1 and key2.
@then
	Ends the condition checking for @if and @elseif sections. If the conditions were true, executes the next block. Otherwise skips to the next @elseif or @else block, or skips past the @endif.
@tobinary(x)
	Converts the integer x to a binary string. @tobinary(255) = 11111111.
@tohex(x)
	Converts the integer x to a hex string. @tohex(255) = FF.
@trim(x)
	Trims any whitespace from the beginning and ending of string x.
@true(x)
	Returns "true" if 'x' is truthy or "false" otherwise.\n\nTruthy values are "true", "t", "yes", "y", "1", "-1", ignoring case.\n\n"null" is neither truthy or falsey and will return "false". Any invalid value will return "false".\n\nThis is exactly the same as "@istrue(x)".
@upper(x)
	Converts all the alphabetic characters in string x to uppercase.
